                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1510">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/162.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reported that Carranza issued orders to Villa today that further investigations
                    of Benton case should cease for present and that Villa refrain from any further
                    discussion of case with either American or British representatives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
